Most Asked Questions
Q-1: where can i get your skin
A-1: OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive OneDrive

Q0: Totori?
A0: one of my friend's former former former former ID was Totori and someday we are memeing at a group so then I changed to that ID lol xd xd

Q1: Hi / Hello
A1: Just get to the point plsssss

Q2: Oh you are in Japan / Netherlands / ??? ?
A2: I use proxy on osu, because you know, Chinese network. The server is actually in Japan, so it may be a glitch that osu shows I'm in NL. btw I don't have any plan to go abroad currently.

Q3: Grip / Area?
A3: Grip: http://ask.fm/rustbell/answers/133720293002#_=_ (The white block was a mobile battery, not the tablet)
Area: Since I don't feel good on ANY area I'm adjusting it from time to time. Apologize that I can't put a archived pic.

Q4: How to aim better / stream faster / play gimmick better / asdfasdfasdf
A4: The advice I can only give is PLAY MORE, since how to get pro on this game was a quite complex stuff.
As for myself, when I get on practicing I usually play what I can't do well (high AR DT or HR). For gimmick maps, basis and rhythm feeling is important imo.

Q5: CAN I GET YOUR MUTUAL?
A5: No. Who are you? I don't add everyone, especially strangers. What's more, what does a single mutual do? Does it make you better at this game? Does it pay you $$$?

Q6: Why do you stop playing mania?
A6: http://ask.fm/rustbell/answers/138176515466

Q7: How do you get 174hz on your monitor?
A7: Add custom resolution on my GPU driver, and also on Custom Resolution Utility (software), modify RefreshRate and OverrideRefreshRate in osu cfg.
Not every 144hz monitor can get 174hz. Afaik BenQ monitors report error even at 145hz.
And I don't think 174hz is very helpful. I actually feel better on a 60hz monitor with less blur.
